{"author":{"id":"78f9c13831d7e4cd23da41f1921a0df29d82a91276573361524e3bf648269089"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782834948,"nonce":"5taY7AXtEHNIb2ro7qiINVOv/oY=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOOEv6_s8AAAABHNAUWg","github-url":"https://github.com/graphcore-research/gwr/issues/185","origin":"github"},"title":"Add recipes to capture demo and document how to use them","message":"Demos:\n\n1) Flow-controlled Pipeline\n - help:\n   cargo run --bin sim-pipe --release -- --help\n\n - defaults achieves 14.9 GiB/s:\n   cargo run --bin sim-pipe --release -- --stdout --progress --binary --perfetto\n   cargo run --release --bin gwr-spotter -- --bin trace.bin\n   open sunburst\n\n - if the buffer weren't large enough:\n   cargo run --bin sim-pipe --release -- --stdout --progress --binary --perfetto --pipe-buffer-entries 5\n   open trace.pftrace\n\n - if the data rates are mismatched:\n   cargo run --bin sim-pipe --release -- --stdout --progress --binary --perfetto --pipe-tx-bits-per-tick 64\n   open trace.pftrace\n\n\n2) Ring simulation (used to understand deadlock scenarios)\n - help:\n   cargo run --release --bin sim-ring -- --help\n\n - show basic structure\n   cargo run --release --bin sim-ring -- --stdout --ring-size 3 --binary-file trace_3.bin --binary --perfetto --progress\n   cargo run --release --bin gwr-spotter -- --bin trace_3.bin\n   open localhost\n     + sunburst\n     + select node0 / tx_buf / show fullness\n     + force_tree\n\n - deadlock\n   cargo run --release --bin sim-ring -- --stdout --ring-size 10 --kib-to-send 1024 --progress --ring-priority 5 --perfetto\n   open trace.pftrace\n   cargo run --release --bin sim-ring -- --stdout --ring-size 10 --kib-to-send 1024 --progress --ring-priority 10\n\n\n3) Fabric simulation with either functional or fully routed models\n - help:\n   cargo run --bin sim-fabric --release -- --help\n\n - basic functions (traffic patterns / fabric size):\n   cargo run --bin sim-fabric --release -- --traffic-pattern all-to-one --stdout --progress --fabric-columns 16 --fabric-rows 16\n   cargo run --bin sim-fabric --release -- --traffic-pattern random --stdout --progress --fabric-columns 16 --fabric-rows 16\n\n - functional vs routed models\n   cargo run --bin sim-fabric --release -- --traffic-pattern random --stdout --progress --fabric-columns 16 --fabric-rows 16 --routed\n   data rate reported significantly lower\n\n - perfetto/binary views\n   cargo run --bin sim-fabric --release -- --traffic-pattern random --stdout --progress --fabric-columns 4 --fabric-rows 2 --routed --binary --binary-file trace_routed.bin --perfetto --perfetto-file trace_routed.pftrace\n   cargo run --release --bin gwr-spotter -- --bin trace_routed.bin\n   open localhost\n   open pftrace","files":null}]}